President Obama has announced the appointment of a Presidential Delegation to Athens, Greece to attend the Special Olympics World Summer Games. Dr. Jill Biden will lead the delegation, and other members include U.S. Ambassador to Greece Daniel B. Smith, Assistant Secretary for Educational and Cultural Affairs Ann Stock, Special Assistant to the President for Disability Policy Kareem Dale, President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities member Micki Edelsohn, Olympic Champion in Gymnastics and Special Olympics Executive Board Member Bart Conner, and Special Olympics Global Manager Kenneth Melvin.